  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "On [line 1060](https://github.com/ethereum/yellowpaper/blob/master/Paper.tex#L1060), it mentions:\r\n\r\n> The longer the path, the greater the total mining effort that must have been done in order to arrive at the leaf.\r\n\r\nThis is not accurate. It is approximately accurate. But since avoiding forks is such an important concept, we should be much more clear here.\r\n\r\nHere is an example that demonstrates the statement is incorrect.\r\n\r\nThe current mainnet block is 5144488. If I fork at block 2000000 and then mine a few blocks slowly wont this change the difficulty level. Eventually I could get up to 5144488 with less mining effort than mainline. That seems to contradict the statement in the text.",
