    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "It's accurate enough. With Bitcoin creating even a single block as a stray miner is an enormous undertaking. Let alone enough before the difficult adjustment drops significantly. But theoretically yeah it's possible, but that's also why Bitcoin clients have [checkpoints](https://bitcoin.stackexchange.com/a/1798).\r\n\r\nEthereum works different anyway with a rule inspired by [GHOST](https://www.cryptocompare.com/coins/guides/what-is-the-ghost-protocol-for-ethereum/).",
