    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I see that uncles can be combined into the current chain if they are within the past 6 generations.\r\n\r\nBut for a new client syncing from scratch... if they would pick the longest chain then I could peer with them and advertise a longer chain than official. And I could do it with with much less resources than a 51% attack.\r\n\r\nI just start at the genesis block and mine at D_0 difficulty. Then when getting closer to current time I make blocks at smaller intervals. The result is I easily get my block count close to mainline and then blow past it in the end.\r\n\r\nEnd result: my pirate chain gets accepted if that yellow paper is followed exactly.\r\n\r\nFix is easy: evaluate the total difficulty of all blocks, not just the height.\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\nAlso, I see equations 43 and 44 both define X. I'll make a PR to fix that.",
